The "Torikku" is written almost the same as the Japanese word "Toritsuku" which means "posession", as in posession by a ghost. In Japanese, the "tsu" in "Toritsuku" is made red, so it looks like it is read as "Torikku". The wordplay only works in Japanese, so the localizers arbitrarily chose a letter to make red in the English title to make the logo asthetically similar.
